On Mon, 24 Aug 2009, Billy Price wrote:

> A lot of them are impractical for, especially moving, vehicles.  C02
> is used for total flooding applications (impractical for bus) and for
> local application, which would still be tough if you were moving.

wouldn't the engine compartment of a bus be "total flood" certainly if
the engine is off, and it would be if the engine compartment were
flooded since the engine wouldn't get any air for combustion.


I've been looking at a 25cu ft boat engine compartment flood system
using FE-241. a manaully discharged system would be about $200.

